selenium, tyrosine and iodine,

00:48:31.590 --> 00:48:35.220
chances are unless there's
an underlying condition there

00:48:35.220 --> 00:48:36.860
that your levels of
thyroid are going to be

00:48:36.860 --> 00:48:38.210
in healthy range.

00:48:38.210 --> 00:48:41.150
Next, we're going to talk
about growth hormone.

00:48:41.150 --> 00:48:43.800
Growth hormone has
received a ton of attention

00:48:43.800 --> 00:48:44.910
in the last 20 years.

00:48:44.910 --> 00:48:47.350
I actually remember when
it was for sequenced.

00:48:47.350 --> 00:48:48.200
This was a huge deal.

00:48:48.200 --> 00:48:50.600
There was a huge patent drama.

00:48:50.600 --> 00:48:52.820
I won't mention the universities
of the people involved.

00:48:52.820 --> 00:48:56.350
There were companies and
monster patents and payouts

00:48:56.350 --> 00:48:57.740
and it was really interesting.

00:48:57.740 --> 00:48:59.240
You can look that up online

00:48:59.240 --> 00:49:01.680
if you're interested in some
of the scientific history.

00:49:01.680 --> 00:49:04.510
Growth hormone is a
pretty straightforward one

00:49:04.510 --> 00:49:06.350
for you to understand
now because it follows

00:49:06.350 --> 00:49:09.300
the exact same logic as thyroid hormone.

00:49:09.300 --> 00:49:13.110
In fact, their functions
are so closely overlapping

00:49:13.110 --> 00:49:15.840
on the, you know, when we
first look at the face of it

00:49:15.840 --> 00:49:16.990
that you're probably going to think,

00:49:16.990 --> 00:49:18.680
why do you have these two systems?

00:49:18.680 --> 00:49:23.680
So just very briefly, growth
hormone-releasing hormone.

00:49:23.890 --> 00:49:25.850
So remember releasing means
it comes from the brain,

00:49:25.850 --> 00:49:28.110
comes from the brain
and tells the pituitary

00:49:28.110 --> 00:49:29.630
to release growth hormone,

00:49:29.630 --> 00:49:31.040
and then growth hormone is released

00:49:31.040 --> 00:49:32.620
into the bloodstream
where it goes and acts

00:49:32.620 --> 00:49:36.000
on a ton of tissues, muscle, ligaments,

00:49:36.000 --> 00:49:39.950
bone, fat, et cetera,
to increase metabolism.

00:49:39.950 --> 00:49:43.460
It sounds just like thyroid hormone.

00:49:43.460 --> 00:49:44.840
And they do work in parallel.

00:49:44.840 --> 00:49:46.060
And that's why we've lumped them together

00:49:46.060 --> 00:49:46.893
in the same episode.

00:49:46.893 --> 00:49:49.200
They increase metabolism and repair

00:49:49.200 --> 00:49:50.453
and growth of tissues.

00:49:52.270 --> 00:49:54.770
A conversation about growth
hormone would be incomplete

00:49:54.770 --> 00:49:56.670
if we didn't talk about
the kind of extremes.

00:49:56.670 --> 00:49:58.180
There are certain people who are born

00:49:58.180 --> 00:50:00.230
that don't make enough growth hormone,

00:50:00.230 --> 00:50:03.100
and they end up very short in stature.

00:50:03.100 --> 00:50:05.697
There are certain people who
make a ton of growth hormone

00:50:05.697 --> 00:50:07.890
and they end up very, very large.

00:50:07.890 --> 00:50:10.170
They tend to have very large appendages.

00:50:10.170 --> 00:50:12.200
They have something called acromegaly.

00:50:12.200 --> 00:50:15.740
It's kind of like a
ridging of the forehead.

00:50:15.740 --> 00:50:17.740
It's actually a bone ridge.

00:50:17.740 --> 00:50:19.060
They are giant.

00:50:19.060 --> 00:50:21.400
And it used to be called giantism.

00:50:21.400 --> 00:50:26.290
And most people of course
are in a range of height

00:50:26.290 --> 00:50:28.170
and appendage length.

00:50:28.170 --> 00:50:29.270
That doesn't imply

00:50:29.270 --> 00:50:31.940
that there's a growth
hormone disruption there.

00:50:31.940 --> 00:50:34.730
Growth hormone received a lot of attention

00:50:34.730 --> 00:50:37.820
after it was sequenced because
that meant the opportunity

00:50:37.820 --> 00:50:40.020
to inject growth hormone

00:50:40.020 --> 00:50:41.890
and replace growth hormone that was lost.

00:50:41.890 --> 00:50:43.890
And there was actually a lot of cases

00:50:43.890 --> 00:50:47.130
of people taking their
kids and trying to get them

00:50:47.130 --> 00:50:49.399
to be taller for whatever reason

00:50:49.399 --> 00:50:51.790
by injecting growth hormone.

00:50:51.790 --> 00:50:53.410
Today, we're going to
talk about the things

00:50:53.410 --> 00:50:56.100
that anyone can do to
increase growth hormone.

00:50:56.100 --> 00:50:57.830
And there are reasons why certain people

00:50:57.830 --> 00:50:58.663
would want to do that.

00:50:58.663 --> 00:51:00.130
People who overproduce growth hormone

00:51:00.130 --> 00:51:01.400
certainly would not want to do that.

00:51:01.400 --> 00:51:05.390
People who underproduce it
would probably want to do that.

00:51:05.390 --> 00:51:08.710
People that make normal, quote, unquote,

00:51:08.710 --> 00:51:11.130
levels of growth hormone
might want to do that

00:51:11.130 --> 00:51:14.970
as they age because during
puberty and development,

00:51:14.970 --> 00:51:17.820
the pituitary is churning
out tons of growth hormone.

00:51:17.820 --> 00:51:20.810
It's responsible for the
growth, not surprising,

00:51:20.810 --> 00:51:23.570
of the body and all its features.

00:51:23.570 --> 00:51:26.200
Height, just being one of those.

00:51:26.200 --> 00:51:29.040
And so as we age, we
make less growth hormone.

00:51:29.040 --> 00:51:31.980
And that is one of the
reasons why we recover

00:51:31.980 --> 00:51:34.240
more slowly from injuries.

00:51:34.240 --> 00:51:37.600
It's one of the reasons
why we accumulate body fat.

00:51:37.600 --> 00:51:40.250
And it's one of the reasons
why our metabolism slows.

00:51:40.250 --> 00:51:42.770
And so growth hormone replacement therapy

00:51:42.770 --> 00:51:46.670
has been tremendously
popular in the last 20 years,

00:51:46.670 --> 00:51:49.520
which is not to say it doesn't
carry its problems, it does.

00:51:49.520 --> 00:51:51.240
Here's one of the major problems

00:51:51.240 --> 00:51:53.490
with injecting growth hormone.

00:51:53.490 --> 00:51:54.920
Not saying people shouldn't do this

00:51:54.920 --> 00:51:57.590
if the doctor has approved
it or it's in keeping

00:51:57.590 --> 00:52:00.000
with their particular life goals,

00:52:00.000 --> 00:52:04.433
but growth hormone, if it's
in levels that are too high,

00:52:05.470 --> 00:52:07.550
will cause growth of all tissues.

00:52:07.550 --> 00:52:09.830
So not just muscle, not just reduction

00:52:09.830 --> 00:52:13.570
in body fat by metabolizing, you know,

00:52:13.570 --> 00:52:16.750
by allowing fatty acids to
be pulled out of storage

00:52:16.750 --> 00:52:20.910
and used for ATP, but it
will also cause increase

00:52:20.910 --> 00:52:22.990
in growth of the heart and the lungs

00:52:22.990 --> 00:52:24.650
and the liver and the spleen.

00:52:24.650 --> 00:52:28.090
And so this is the concern
with abuse of growth hormone.

00:52:28.090 --> 00:52:29.030
So we're not going to be talking

00:52:29.030 --> 00:52:30.140
about abuse of growth hormone.

00:52:30.140 --> 00:52:33.720
We will, however, talk about
tools that anyone can use

00:52:33.720 --> 00:52:35.880
to increase levels of growth hormone.

00:52:35.880 --> 00:52:36.930
Some of them are behavioral,

00:52:36.930 --> 00:52:38.630
some of them are supplement-based

00:52:38.630 --> 00:52:42.280
and some of them interact with
behaviors and supplements.

00:52:42.280 --> 00:52:44.370
And what's cool about the discussion

00:52:44.370 --> 00:52:46.820
about growth hormone is that the tools

00:52:46.820 --> 00:52:48.980
that exist out there to
increase growth hormone

00:52:48.980 --> 00:52:50.940
are very actionable.

00:52:50.940 --> 00:52:52.720
Most people can do these without the need

00:52:52.720 --> 00:52:54.420
for any equipment or even any supplement.

00:52:54.420 --> 00:52:57.890
Although there are some
supplement related themes

00:52:57.890 --> 00:53:00.090
for tools for growth hormone increase.

00:53:00.090 --> 00:53:02.720
And also the increases that one can get

00:53:02.720 --> 00:53:05.230
in growth hormone are substantial.

00:53:05.230 --> 00:53:07.490
So normally, when you
talk about the difference

00:53:07.490 --> 00:53:10.370
between taking something
as an exogenous substance

00:53:11.290 --> 00:53:14.310
like testosterone or estrogen
versus using supplements

00:53:14.310 --> 00:53:15.880
or behaviors to increase them,

00:53:15.880 --> 00:53:19.130
you're talking about tenfold
differences from, you know,

00:53:19.130 --> 00:53:21.880
administering the prescription compound.

00:53:21.880 --> 00:53:22.920
In terms of growth hormone,

00:53:22.920 --> 00:53:25.530
there are things that can
increase growth hormone three,

00:53:25.530 --> 00:53:29.090
four, 500% or more.

00:53:29.090 --> 00:53:32.230
And even though that's
a short-lived increase,

00:53:32.230 --> 00:53:33.570
they can have very powerful effects

00:53:33.570 --> 00:53:35.860
on metabolism and on repair of tissues.

00:53:35.860 --> 00:53:37.480
So let's talk about those.

00:53:37.480 --> 00:53:40.540
Okay, let's go step by
step in terms of the things

00:53:40.540 --> 00:53:42.500
that anyone, perhaps everyone,

00:53:42.500 --> 00:53:44.670
should be doing in order to maintain

00:53:44.670 --> 00:53:46.020
healthy growth hormone levels

00:53:46.020 --> 00:53:48.200
or increased growth hormone levels.

00:53:48.200 --> 00:53:51.270
Unless you have overproduction
of growth hormone,

00:53:51.270 --> 00:53:54.313
chances are these things
are going to benefit to you.

00:53:55.290 --> 00:53:58.010
However, as always, I want to emphasize,

00:53:58.010 --> 00:54:00.750
talk to a doctor before you do anything,

00:54:00.750 --> 00:54:03.340
including remove any treatments.

00:54:03.340 --> 00:54:06.150
So anything you would add or take away,

00:54:06.150 --> 00:54:07.790
that's the responsibility of you

00:54:07.790 --> 00:54:09.550
and your healthcare provider, okay?

00:54:09.550 --> 00:54:10.850
I don't just say that to protect me,

00:54:10.850 --> 00:54:12.960
I say that to protect you.

00:54:12.960 --> 00:54:15.740
First of all, growth hormone is released

00:54:15.740 --> 00:54:17.570
every night when you go to sleep

00:54:17.570 --> 00:54:20.170
and it's released in
the early part of sleep,

00:54:20.170 --> 00:54:22.073
during so-called slow-wave sleep.

00:54:23.030 --> 00:54:25.800
So the two conditions that have to be met

00:54:25.800 --> 00:54:29.210
in order for growth hormone
to be secreted regularly

00:54:29.210 --> 00:54:31.620
for tissue repair, et cetera,

00:54:31.620 --> 00:54:34.610
are you need to get into slow-wave sleep

00:54:34.610 --> 00:54:39.410
that so-called deep sleep
and you need blood insulin

00:54:39.410 --> 00:54:41.800
and glucose to be relatively low.

00:54:41.800 --> 00:54:44.740
So eating within two hours of sleep,

00:54:44.740 --> 00:54:47.300
excuse me, eating within
two hours of going to sleep

00:54:47.300 --> 00:54:49.200
is going to suppress
growth hormone release.

00:54:49.200 --> 00:54:50.690
That's very clear.

00:54:50.690 --> 00:54:52.970
However, some people are
going to have problems

00:54:52.970 --> 00:54:55.470
falling asleep if they are too hungry.

00:54:55.470 --> 00:54:56.970
So you have to work with that

00:54:56.970 --> 00:54:59.520
and decide what you're going to eat.

00:54:59.520 --> 00:55:01.420
And when you're going to eat that thing

00:55:01.420 --> 00:55:02.640
so that you're not so hungry

00:55:02.640 --> 00:55:04.840
that you're having trouble falling asleep.

00:55:04.840 --> 00:55:06.660
The episodes on sleep that were covered

00:55:06.660 --> 00:55:09.760
in episodes two, three, and
four of the Huberman Lab Podcast

00:55:09.760 --> 00:55:13.160
has, I believe, more tools
there than you could ever want

00:55:13.160 --> 00:55:15.460
or make use of in terms
of how to optimize sleep.

00:55:15.460 --> 00:55:17.620
So you can refer to those, if you like.

00:55:17.620 --> 00:55:19.850
So don't eat too close to sleep

00:55:19.850 --> 00:55:21.430
and then get into slow-wave sleep.

00:55:21.430 --> 00:55:24.350
And as I talked about in one
of those earlier episodes,

00:55:24.350 --> 00:55:25.820
the first half of the night,

00:55:25.820 --> 00:55:28.380
slow-wave sleep and
deep sleep predominate.

00:55:28.380 --> 00:55:29.270
The second half of the night,

00:55:29.270 --> 00:55:31.910
it's another kind of sleep,
we call it REM sleep.

00:55:31.910 --> 00:55:36.050
So what is special about
this early phase of sleep?

00:55:36.050 --> 00:55:37.370
This is how you should be thinking

00:55:37.370 --> 00:55:39.200
if you listen to this podcast.

00:55:39.200 --> 00:55:40.400
You should be thinking, okay,

00:55:40.400 --> 00:55:41.960
I hear that something is important,

00:55:41.960 --> 00:55:43.560
it's related, it's in the pathway,

00:55:43.560 --> 00:55:46.680
but mechanistically when we
say get into slow-wave sleep,

00:55:46.680 --> 00:55:48.080
get into deep sleep,

00:55:48.080 --> 00:55:49.990
that's when growth hormone is secreted.

00:55:49.990 --> 00:55:51.750
The question you should
be asking yourselves

00:55:51.750 --> 00:55:56.750
as scientists of yourselves
is wait, why slow-wave sleep?

00:55:57.670 --> 00:56:01.470
What in particular about
slow-wave deep sleep

00:56:01.470 --> 00:56:04.400
allows the pituitary to
release growth hormone?

00:56:04.400 --> 00:56:06.410
Like, what is it?

00:56:06.410 --> 00:56:08.270
Because if you can understand that,

00:56:08.270 --> 00:56:10.490
if you can understand a
little bit of mechanism,

00:56:10.490 --> 00:56:12.800
there are actually ways
that you can increase

00:56:12.800 --> 00:56:15.810
the amount of growth
hormone that you release

00:56:15.810 --> 00:56:18.260
both in sleep and out of sleep.

00:56:18.260 --> 00:56:22.610
So the answer is it's delta
wave activity in the brain.

00:56:22.610 --> 00:56:26.320
Delta waves are these big
giant waves of activity

00:56:26.320 --> 00:56:29.930
in the brain that correlate
with slow-wave sleep

00:56:29.930 --> 00:56:31.560
as opposed to faster waves of activity

00:56:31.560 --> 00:56:34.450
that is associated with
rapid eye movement sleep.

00:56:34.450 --> 00:56:37.810
So slow-wave sleep and the delta activity

00:56:37.810 --> 00:56:40.810
actually triggers the
neurons in the brain,

00:56:40.810 --> 00:56:42.580
the releasing hormone, right?

00:56:42.580 --> 00:56:44.380
Growth hormone-releasing hormone neurons

00:56:44.380 --> 00:56:46.040
to signal to the pituitary.

00:56:46.040 --> 00:56:47.320
Now, how do I know this is true?

00:56:47.320 --> 00:56:48.230
And what can you do with this?

00:56:48.230 --> 00:56:49.130
Well, we know this is true

00:56:49.130 --> 00:56:50.937
because researchers have taken people

00:56:50.937 --> 00:56:54.750
and sleep deprived them,
and they just asked, well,

00:56:54.750 --> 00:56:57.100
is it just one period
of time every 24 hours

00:56:57.100 --> 00:56:59.260
and then the pituitary
releases growth hormone?

00:56:59.260 --> 00:57:00.930
If that were the case, that would say

00:57:00.930 --> 00:57:02.680
that growth hormone is just released

00:57:02.680 --> 00:57:05.400
in a so-called circadian dependent way.

00:57:05.400 --> 00:57:08.460
Every 24 hours is the pulse of it, but no,

00:57:08.460 --> 00:57:10.680
it's always relating to slow-wave

00:57:10.680 --> 00:57:12.420
deep sleep and delta waves.

00:57:12.420 --> 00:57:14.410
And this is cool because what it means

00:57:14.410 --> 00:57:16.470
is that even if you're not
measuring your brainwaves

00:57:16.470 --> 00:57:19.490
during sleep, which most
of you probably are not,

00:57:19.490 --> 00:57:21.040
you might be measuring slow-wave sleep

00:57:21.040 --> 00:57:24.060
or deep sleep using a
device like a Whoop or Oura.

00:57:24.060 --> 00:57:26.230
And even if you're not,

00:57:26.230 --> 00:57:29.500
what this means is that during the day,

00:57:29.500 --> 00:57:30.440
there's the potential

00:57:30.440 --> 00:57:33.380
to also increase growth hormone release

00:57:33.380 --> 00:57:36.480
if you can get the brain into
the so-called delta waves.

00:57:36.480 --> 00:57:38.300
And it turns out there
are things you can do

00:57:38.300 --> 00:57:41.310
in waking as well to increase
growth hormone release.

00:57:41.310 --> 00:57:42.890
So we're going to talk about those next.

00:57:42.890 --> 00:57:45.330
But as a tool and to just really make sure

00:57:45.330 --> 00:57:47.200
that we put brackets around this,

00:57:47.200 --> 00:57:49.380
try and have blood glucose not too high.

00:57:49.380 --> 00:57:50.840
So if you do need to eat close to bed,

00:57:50.840 --> 00:57:52.020
you wouldn't want to eat anything

00:57:52.020 --> 00:57:54.610
that would increase
blood glucose too much.

00:57:54.610 --> 00:57:57.080
Try not to eat too close to bedtime.

00:57:57.080 --> 00:57:59.010
Get into deep sleep early in the night.

00:57:59.010 --> 00:58:00.990
Get the growth hormone release.

00:58:00.990 --> 00:58:03.970
And understand that it's
the delta waves of activity,

00:58:03.970 --> 00:58:06.190
the sweeping big waves of
activity in the neurons

00:58:06.190 --> 00:58:08.373
that stimulate the brain
to stimulate the pituitary.

00:58:08.373 --> 00:58:10.570
Because once you understand that,

00:58:10.570 --> 00:58:11.940
then you have something to anchor to

00:58:11.940 --> 00:58:14.480
in terms of thinking what
are the things I can do

00:58:14.480 --> 00:58:18.190
in waking that will allow me
to release more growth hormone

00:58:18.190 --> 00:58:20.970
which for most people is
going to be a good thing.

