higher doses in most supplements

00:58:53.110 --> 00:58:57.240
than one would normally make
like a hundred fold, 300 fold.

00:58:57.240 --> 00:59:00.250
However, today I'm going
to talk about an instance

00:59:00.250 --> 00:59:03.870
where very low levels of
melatonin supplementation

00:59:03.870 --> 00:59:06.170
might actually be advantageous.

00:59:06.170 --> 00:59:08.900
And that is aiding the transition

00:59:08.900 --> 00:59:12.080
to the delta wave, slow-wave
sleep I just described

00:59:12.080 --> 00:59:14.010
because that's the pattern of sleep

00:59:14.010 --> 00:59:17.940
and brainwave activity that
triggers growth hormone release.

00:59:17.940 --> 00:59:21.530
So whereas most melatonin
supplements are one milligram,

00:59:21.530 --> 00:59:24.920
three milligrams, 12
milligrams, this kind of thing,

00:59:24.920 --> 00:59:27.330
that is super physiological.

00:59:27.330 --> 00:59:30.330
There are some data
showing that microgram,

00:59:30.330 --> 00:59:35.330
maybe 500 micrograms of
melatonin, so half a milligram,

00:59:36.400 --> 00:59:38.970
can be beneficial in shifting the pattern

00:59:38.970 --> 00:59:41.550
of early night's sleep
toward more of the slow-wave

00:59:41.550 --> 00:59:43.650
deep sleep delta activity

00:59:43.650 --> 00:59:45.930
and improving growth hormone release.

00:59:45.930 --> 00:59:49.610
Not a lot of studies but the
ones that I saw are quality.

00:59:49.610 --> 00:59:52.210
They were done in subjects that, you know,

00:59:52.210 --> 00:59:55.660
both sexes, sufficient numbers, et cetera.

00:59:55.660 --> 00:59:56.580
So this is interesting.

00:59:56.580 --> 01:00:00.020
So if you're interested in
melatonin supplementation,

01:00:00.020 --> 01:00:03.250
you might think about it
just at very low levels.

01:00:03.250 --> 01:00:05.130
You know, hundreds of micrograms

01:00:05.130 --> 01:00:06.990
as opposed to the milligram dosages.

01:00:06.990 --> 01:00:08.430
Most of the ones out there

01:00:08.430 --> 01:00:10.300
are going to be in milligram dosages.

01:00:10.300 --> 01:00:14.660
So that's one way that
some studies have shown

01:00:14.660 --> 01:00:17.080
that you can increase the
amount of growth hormone

01:00:17.080 --> 01:00:19.970
that's secreted in early phases of sleep.

01:00:19.970 --> 01:00:23.020
Now, the delta wave activity
and the slow-wave activity

01:00:23.020 --> 01:00:25.830
in the brain being very important

01:00:25.830 --> 01:00:28.360
for growth hormone release
and growth hormone release

01:00:28.360 --> 01:00:30.830
being so important for metabolic functions

01:00:30.830 --> 01:00:33.410
and peeling away unwanted body fat

01:00:33.410 --> 01:00:35.840
and repairing tissues, et cetera,

01:00:35.840 --> 01:00:38.630
forces us to ask, well,
what other things can we do

01:00:38.630 --> 01:00:41.980
in waking in order to increase
growth hormone release?

01:00:41.980 --> 01:00:42.813
So let's start

01:00:42.813 --> 01:00:46.540
with the ones that have
a potentially big effect

01:00:46.540 --> 01:00:48.400
but are a little bit harder to access.

01:00:48.400 --> 01:00:51.210
And for that, I want
to point toward a book,

01:00:51.210 --> 01:00:52.710
which is really kind of interesting.

01:00:52.710 --> 01:00:54.470
It's not focused on growth hormone

01:00:54.470 --> 01:00:57.000
but the book is called "Altered Traits."

01:00:57.000 --> 01:00:58.480
This is the book.

01:00:58.480 --> 01:01:00.287
It's an excellent book,

01:01:00.287 --> 01:01:03.087
"Altered Traits" by Goleman and Davidson.

01:01:03.087 --> 01:01:04.860
"Science Reveals How Meditation

01:01:04.860 --> 01:01:07.410
Changes Your Mind, Brain, and Body."

01:01:07.410 --> 01:01:09.120
Very interesting book.

01:01:09.120 --> 01:01:11.550
For those of you that are
interested in meditation,

01:01:11.550 --> 01:01:14.170
and perhaps those of you who are not,

01:01:14.170 --> 01:01:15.946
but are considering it,

01:01:15.946 --> 01:01:18.250
what they talk about in
this book is the fact

01:01:18.250 --> 01:01:21.170
that meditation has two
separate lines of effects.

01:01:21.170 --> 01:01:23.870
One of those lines of effects are things

01:01:23.870 --> 01:01:25.260
that change your state.

01:01:25.260 --> 01:01:26.580
So you're stressed.

01:01:26.580 --> 01:01:27.910
You sit down, you meditate

01:01:27.910 --> 01:01:29.890
and you relax and you go
into a particular state.

01:01:29.890 --> 01:01:32.660
The other are the changes
that occur over time

01:01:32.660 --> 01:01:34.650
and those are changes in trait.

01:01:34.650 --> 01:01:36.720
So personality can actually change

01:01:36.720 --> 01:01:41.720
with long bouts of TM meditation
or repeated meditation.

01:01:42.870 --> 01:01:44.090
In any case, the reason we're talking

01:01:44.090 --> 01:01:49.090
about "Altered Traits" today
is because certain types

01:01:49.110 --> 01:01:52.760
of meditation can get people's brains

01:01:52.760 --> 01:01:56.590
into states that very closely
mimic slow-wave sleep.

01:01:56.590 --> 01:01:59.700
If you hear snoring in the
background, Costello is,

01:01:59.700 --> 01:02:01.470
sounds like he's in slow-wave sleep.

01:02:01.470 --> 01:02:04.320
These big oscillatory snores

01:02:04.320 --> 01:02:07.970
that he's in 23.6 hours per day.

01:02:07.970 --> 01:02:11.340
So what this means is for
people that are interested

01:02:11.340 --> 01:02:14.930
in increasing growth hormone,
a meditation practice

01:02:14.930 --> 01:02:19.930
that allows you to get into
these slow-wave delta type

01:02:20.080 --> 01:02:24.810
frequency activity in the
brain may be very beneficial

01:02:24.810 --> 01:02:25.900
because as I mentioned before,

01:02:25.900 --> 01:02:28.060
that's what's gating
growth hormone release.

01:02:28.060 --> 01:02:29.900
It's not just a circadian phenomenon,

01:02:29.900 --> 01:02:33.010
it's actually controlled
by these brainwaves.

01:02:33.010 --> 01:02:34.970
I did look up binaural beats.

01:02:34.970 --> 01:02:36.970
I get so many questions
about binaural beats

01:02:36.970 --> 01:02:38.730
and it's a really attractive idea, right?

01:02:38.730 --> 01:02:39.940
Binaural beats, for
those of you don't know,

01:02:39.940 --> 01:02:43.090
you listen to one frequency
of tone in one ear

01:02:43.090 --> 01:02:45.370
and another frequency of
tone and the other ear,

01:02:45.370 --> 01:02:50.110
and then the brain essentially
takes the average of the two

01:02:50.110 --> 01:02:52.870
or there's some other
wiring in the brainstem

01:02:52.870 --> 01:02:54.060
that makes it not quite the average

01:02:54.060 --> 01:02:57.600
but it takes the average of
the two for sake of discussion.

01:02:57.600 --> 01:03:00.310
And that frequency is
what the brain entrains

01:03:00.310 --> 01:03:01.930
or maps onto.

01:03:01.930 --> 01:03:03.840
There are a lot of apps that are claiming

01:03:03.840 --> 01:03:05.840
that you can get the
brain into delta waves

01:03:05.840 --> 01:03:06.910
using binaural beats.

01:03:06.910 --> 01:03:09.880
I could not find quality
peer review studies

01:03:09.880 --> 01:03:11.930
supporting that, but I know
there are a lot of fans

01:03:11.930 --> 01:03:13.260
out there of binaural beats.

01:03:13.260 --> 01:03:14.660
If you know of any literature

01:03:14.660 --> 01:03:16.500
that's independent of the company

01:03:16.500 --> 01:03:18.690
that makes the binaural beat technology,

01:03:18.690 --> 01:03:22.010
so unbiased research,
please send it my way.

01:03:22.010 --> 01:03:26.580
But in "Altered Traits,"
Goleman and Davidson

01:03:26.580 --> 01:03:29.360
talk about the fact that
people who do 20 minutes

01:03:29.360 --> 01:03:31.970
of sitting meditation per day

01:03:31.970 --> 01:03:36.970
can access these slow-wave
sleep like brain states.

01:03:37.110 --> 01:03:38.320
Now, I've talked a lot on here

01:03:38.320 --> 01:03:40.410
about non-sleep deep rest,

01:03:40.410 --> 01:03:42.650
things like yoga nidra and hypnosis.

01:03:42.650 --> 01:03:44.600
I'm not aware that those will put people

01:03:44.600 --> 01:03:48.890
into slow-wave sleep per
se, or delta waves per se.

01:03:48.890 --> 01:03:50.420
So we're really talking about 20 minutes

01:03:50.420 --> 01:03:52.300
of more traditional type meditation.

01:03:52.300 --> 01:03:55.750
Okay, so we've talked about
very low doses of melatonin

01:03:55.750 --> 01:03:57.250
as a way to trigger delta waves

01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.640
and more growth hormone release in sleep.

01:03:59.640 --> 01:04:00.860
There's science to support that.

01:04:00.860 --> 01:04:05.140
We've now talked about a
waking behavior of 20 minutes

01:04:05.140 --> 01:04:08.050
of sort of what I would
call standard meditation

01:04:08.050 --> 01:04:10.030
or just sitting there,
concentrating on one's breathing

01:04:10.030 --> 01:04:12.340
to try and access delta waves.

01:04:12.340 --> 01:04:14.860
Binaural beats, no science yet.

01:04:14.860 --> 01:04:15.693
Who knows?

01:04:15.693 --> 01:04:17.310
Maybe there's science to support it.

01:04:17.310 --> 01:04:18.940
If you're aware of it, let me know.

01:04:18.940 --> 01:04:21.620
Now, let's move to the
things that one can do

01:04:21.620 --> 01:04:25.130
that have been shown to have
what's, let's just be honest,

01:04:25.130 --> 01:04:29.080
pretty enormous effects on
growth hormone release in waking.

01:04:29.080 --> 01:04:31.930
And these are things
that are very actionable.

01:04:31.930 --> 01:04:34.290
One of the things that
can have a dramatic effect

01:04:34.290 --> 01:04:37.110
on levels of growth
hormone release in waking

01:04:37.110 --> 01:04:42.050
as well as in sleep the
following night is exercise.

01:04:42.050 --> 01:04:46.630
But the key is the type of
exercise and the duration.

01:04:46.630 --> 01:04:48.910
Now, there's a logic to this.

01:04:48.910 --> 01:04:51.340
There are hundreds, if
not thousands of studies

01:04:51.340 --> 01:04:53.210
measuring growth hormone,

01:04:53.210 --> 01:04:57.480
both during or sometimes after exercise

01:04:57.480 --> 01:04:59.780
or the following night.

01:04:59.780 --> 01:05:02.500
And the conclusion that one takes away

01:05:02.500 --> 01:05:05.140
from all of these is that exercise

01:05:05.140 --> 01:05:08.640
has to be of particular
duration and intensity

01:05:08.640 --> 01:05:10.810
in order to get growth hormone release.

01:05:10.810 --> 01:05:12.560
So first I'm just going to tell you

01:05:12.560 --> 01:05:14.570
what I found to be the maximum amount

01:05:14.570 --> 01:05:15.930
of growth hormone release

01:05:15.930 --> 01:05:18.910
as it relates to a
particular form of exercise.

01:05:18.910 --> 01:05:22.280
The particular form of exercise
is either weight training

01:05:23.210 --> 01:05:25.850
or it can be endurance training,

01:05:25.850 --> 01:05:28.170
but the endurance training
and the weight training

01:05:28.170 --> 01:05:31.460
actually have to be limited
to about 60 minutes,

01:05:31.460 --> 01:05:32.340
not much longer.

01:05:32.340 --> 01:05:34.350
Now, this is important

01:05:34.350 --> 01:05:37.350
because it's been shown
over and over again

01:05:37.350 --> 01:05:40.590
that if one exercises
too long with weights

01:05:40.590 --> 01:05:44.620
or endurance exercise, that
cortisol levels go high enough

01:05:44.620 --> 01:05:47.540
that it starts to inhibit the testosterone

01:05:47.540 --> 01:05:49.700
and even the estrogen pathways.

01:05:49.700 --> 01:05:53.460
This is why I believe
people who overexercise

01:05:53.460 --> 01:05:55.800
or exercise a lot can lose
their menstrual cycles.

01:05:55.800 --> 01:05:57.180
They stop menstruating.

01:05:57.180 --> 01:05:59.090
It's why you get
suppressions in testosterone

01:05:59.090 --> 01:06:01.400
if people train too long and too hard.

01:06:01.400 --> 01:06:02.970
The cutoff has always been, you know,

01:06:02.970 --> 01:06:06.370
60 to 75 minutes of the hard work part.

01:06:06.370 --> 01:06:08.830
It's going to vary a lot
from person to person,

01:06:08.830 --> 01:06:10.770
but in terms of growth hormone,

01:06:10.770 --> 01:06:12.570
the conditions that seem to lead

01:06:12.570 --> 01:06:17.570
to the greatest growth hormone
releases are one, get warm.

01:06:17.780 --> 01:06:19.410
This is interesting, we're
going to talk about temperature.

01:06:19.410 --> 01:06:23.030
So a proper warmup seems to accelerate

01:06:23.030 --> 01:06:24.880
the release of growth hormone

01:06:24.880 --> 01:06:27.280
once the hard work phase starts.

01:06:27.280 --> 01:06:30.570
So 10 minutes of warmup
or so was the number

01:06:30.570 --> 01:06:33.000
that I extracted from all these studies.

01:06:33.000 --> 01:06:35.920
There's a beautiful review
on this, by the way.

01:06:35.920 --> 01:06:38.983
Growth hormone responses
of varying, excuse me,

01:06:40.527 --> 01:06:43.310
"Growth hormone, arginine and exercise."

01:06:43.310 --> 01:06:44.960
We'll talk about arginine
in a few minutes.

01:06:44.960 --> 01:06:49.930
That's by Kanaley, K-A-N-A-L-E-Y.

01:06:49.930 --> 01:06:51.940
It was published in Current Opinion

01:06:51.940 --> 01:06:54.520
in Clinical Nutrition and Metabolic Care.

01:06:54.520 --> 01:06:56.700
The Current Opinion journals are generally

01:06:56.700 --> 01:07:00.150
of pretty high quality
in terms of the reviews

01:07:00.150 --> 01:07:01.830
just because they tend
to be pretty recent.

01:07:01.830 --> 01:07:06.170
And then the references
therein are also quite good.

01:07:06.170 --> 01:07:07.560
So what does this mean?

01:07:07.560 --> 01:07:08.910
This means warm up.

01:07:08.910 --> 01:07:09.900
And when you say warm up,

01:07:09.900 --> 01:07:12.600
it doesn't mean just warm
up the limbs and tissues

01:07:12.600 --> 01:07:14.130
that you're going to use
so you don't get injured,

01:07:14.130 --> 01:07:15.990
actually warm the body.

01:07:15.990 --> 01:07:17.580
So there was actually some discussion

01:07:17.580 --> 01:07:19.420
about whether or not
in cold winter months,

01:07:19.420 --> 01:07:21.900
people should wear like a stocking cap,

01:07:21.900 --> 01:07:25.240
bringing the conditions,
making the room warm.

01:07:25.240 --> 01:07:28.410
So getting the body warm as a
warmup seems to be important

01:07:28.410 --> 01:07:30.400
because temperature of the body

01:07:30.400 --> 01:07:32.640
seems to be an important condition

01:07:32.640 --> 01:07:35.630
or prerequisite for certain
patterns of exercise

01:07:35.630 --> 01:07:37.760
to maximize growth hormone release.

01:07:37.760 --> 01:07:40.000
So it's really interesting to me.

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:41.970
I have an obsession with
how body temperature,

01:07:41.970 --> 01:07:44.110
light exercise and food interact.

01:07:44.110 --> 01:07:47.650
We're going right there with
the fact that if you get warm,

01:07:47.650 --> 01:07:49.190
you bring up the body temperature

01:07:49.190 --> 01:07:53.810
a degree or two or maybe
three, and then start exercise.

01:07:53.810 --> 01:07:57.640
It does appear that
high-intensity exercise,

01:07:57.640 --> 01:08:01.190
but again as discussed
in a previous episode,

01:08:01.190 --> 01:08:05.260
not exercise that brings
muscles to failure

01:08:05.260 --> 01:08:06.270
but close to it.

01:08:06.270 --> 01:08:08.120
So if it's weight-bearing exercise,

01:08:08.120 --> 01:08:11.150
it would be getting close
to that final repetitions

01:08:11.150 --> 01:08:12.190
where you can't complete them

01:08:12.190 --> 01:08:14.710
but not pushing through those
or even going to failure

01:08:14.710 --> 01:08:17.520
but getting close leads to anywhere

01:08:17.520 --> 01:08:21.990
from 300 to 500% increases in
resting growth hormone levels

01:08:21.990 --> 01:08:26.090
and 300 to 500% increases
in growth hormone

01:08:26.090 --> 01:08:28.340
the following night when you go to sleep,

01:08:28.340 --> 01:08:30.260
which is incredible.

01:08:30.260 --> 01:08:32.960
Now, I want to dissect this properly.

01:08:32.960 --> 01:08:35.910
Okay, so one of the other conditions

01:08:35.910 --> 01:08:37.520
that seem to be important, again,

01:08:37.520 --> 01:08:40.490
was to have relatively low blood glucose.

01:08:40.490 --> 01:08:42.530
So it's looking a lot like
the conditions you need

01:08:42.530 --> 01:08:44.250
for sleep in order to get maximum

01:08:44.250 --> 01:08:46.000
growth hormone release in sleep.

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:49.143
So not having blood glucose
too high or too low,

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:51.610
that's a discussion unto itself.

01:08:51.610 --> 01:08:54.250
You want to have sufficient
energy to do the exercise

01:08:54.250 --> 01:08:55.290
but getting warm,

01:08:55.290 --> 01:08:57.230
not having blood glucose
too high or too low.

01:08:57.230 --> 01:08:59.790
So probably not eating
too close to exercise

01:08:59.790 --> 01:09:04.300
or not in ingesting a lot of
sugars during the exercise.

01:09:04.300 --> 01:09:06.310
That was supported by
the fact that ingestion

01:09:06.310 --> 01:09:09.350
of a sports drink that
contains caloric sugar

01:09:09.350 --> 01:09:12.260
immediately flat-line the
growth hormone levels.

01:09:12.260 --> 01:09:14.190
So really interesting relationship

01:09:14.190 --> 01:09:17.070
between insulin, glucose
and growth hormone.

01:09:17.070 --> 01:09:19.190
So then doing the training for anywhere

01:09:19.190 --> 01:09:23.080
from 60 to 75 minutes to
maximize growth hormone release.

01:09:23.080 --> 01:09:25.930
And then the other interesting thing

01:09:25.930 --> 01:09:28.590
was that even after the exercise,

01:09:28.590 --> 01:09:30.630
taking body temperature back down

01:09:30.630 --> 01:09:35.140
to normal levels relatively
quickly seemed to be associated

01:09:35.140 --> 01:09:37.160
with these big spikes in growth hormone.

01:09:37.160 --> 01:09:39.090
Otherwise, what would happen
is you get these big spikes

01:09:39.090 --> 01:09:42.000
in growth hormone, but if
the exercise went too long

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:44.790
or if body temperature
remained too high for too long,

01:09:44.790 --> 01:09:46.760
then you didn't get the second increase

01:09:46.760 --> 01:09:48.930
in growth hormone the
following night, okay?

01:09:48.930 --> 01:09:50.730
So I hope I made that abundantly clear.

01:09:50.730 --> 01:09:53.160
Warm up well, get body temperature up,

01:09:53.160 --> 01:09:55.600
exercise 60 to 75 minutes.

01:09:55.600 --> 01:09:57.110
Don't go to absolute failure

01:09:57.110 --> 01:10:00.860
if your interest is in
growth hormone release

01:10:00.860 --> 01:10:04.210
both during the exercise
and later that night.

01:10:04.210 --> 01:10:07.320
And if you can bring body
temperature back down

01:10:07.320 --> 01:10:08.820
to normal levels by cooling off,

01:10:08.820 --> 01:10:11.080
maybe cool shower or maybe
ice pack or something,

01:10:11.080 --> 01:10:14.010
or maybe just turning
off the heat in the room

01:10:14.010 --> 01:10:15.840
or going outside, whatever it is,

01:10:15.840 --> 01:10:17.420
then you increase the probability

01:10:17.420 --> 01:10:19.720
that you're going to
increase growth hormone

01:10:19.720 --> 01:10:21.600
the following night as well.

01:10:21.600 --> 01:10:24.210
And again, these are big
increases, 300 to 500%.

01:10:24.210 --> 01:10:25.050
It's almost like you're getting

01:10:25.050 --> 01:10:27.390
a second sleep during the day.

01:10:27.390 --> 01:10:29.670
But if the exercise is too
hard, if body temperature

01:10:29.670 --> 01:10:33.180
stays too high for too long,
you disrupt the whole process

01:10:33.180 --> 01:10:35.850
and you don't get the effect
of increased growth hormone.

01:10:35.850 --> 01:10:37.420
Growth hormone is really powerful

01:10:37.420 --> 01:10:39.100
but it doesn't work alone.

01:10:39.100 --> 01:10:42.130
In fact, a lot of the effects
of growth hormone are mediated

01:10:42.130 --> 01:10:43.700
by its effects on the liver.

01:10:43.700 --> 01:10:45.610
So growth hormone is
released, goes to the liver,

01:10:45.610 --> 01:10:47.980
and then the liver releases
something called IGF-1,

01:10:47.980 --> 01:10:50.450
insulin growth factor 1.

01:10:50.450 --> 01:10:53.430
Insulin growth factor 1 was popular

01:10:53.430 --> 01:10:55.720
in the neuroscience
community as an area of focus

01:10:55.720 --> 01:10:58.290
because of its ability
to trigger improvements

01:10:58.290 --> 01:11:01.410
in memory and learning after exercise.

01:11:01.410 --> 01:11:03.080
And indeed exercise triggers

01:11:03.080 --> 01:11:05.774
both the release of
growth hormone and IGF-1.

01:11:05.774 --> 01:11:08.710
IGF-1 seems responsible
for a lot of the effects

01:11:08.710 --> 01:11:10.600
of improved memory.

01:11:10.600 --> 01:11:13.050
Some people report that that is due

01:11:13.050 --> 01:11:15.690
to increased number of
neurons or neurogenesis,

01:11:15.690 --> 01:11:16.570
birth of new neurons.

01:11:16.570 --> 01:11:18.210
It's pretty clear that in humans,

01:11:18.210 --> 01:11:19.870
that's not what's happening.

01:11:19.870 --> 01:11:21.260
Yes in animals, not in humans.

01:11:21.260 --> 01:11:23.480
IGF-1 nonetheless has positive effects

01:11:23.480 --> 01:11:25.290
on memory and cognition.

01:11:25.290 --> 01:11:27.147
And a great way to trigger IGF-1 release

01:11:27.147 --> 01:11:30.520
and growth hormone release
is through exercise.

01:11:30.520 --> 01:11:32.510
Now, the interesting thing,

01:11:32.510 --> 01:11:35.050
and the reason I'm bringing up IGF-1 here

01:11:35.050 --> 01:11:37.500
is that certain patterns of exercise,

01:11:37.500 --> 01:11:40.500
actually duration of exercise
have different effects

01:11:40.500 --> 01:11:42.463
on IGF-1 and growth hormone,

01:11:43.390 --> 01:11:45.810
depending on whether or not the exercise

01:11:45.810 --> 01:11:47.590
is done by men or women.

01:11:47.590 --> 01:11:50.550
There's what we call sex-dependent effect.

01:11:50.550 --> 01:11:53.820
And the sex-dependent
effect is as follows.

01:11:53.820 --> 01:11:56.000
In this particular study
and several others,

01:11:56.000 --> 01:11:58.480
what they did is they had people exercise.

01:11:58.480 --> 01:12:01.760
They measured growth
hormone and IGF-1 levels

01:12:01.760 --> 01:12:05.690
from the blood before,
during and after exercise.

01:12:05.690 --> 01:12:08.390
And they could see when the
greatest increases occurred.

01:12:08.390 --> 01:12:11.750
This was standard sorts
of resistance exercise.

01:12:11.750 --> 01:12:12.843
So some squats.

01:12:13.710 --> 01:12:17.350
There was a sprint like activity.

01:12:17.350 --> 01:12:21.830
It doesn't really matter what
the specific exercises were.

01:12:21.830 --> 01:12:22.930
None of them were to failure.

01:12:22.930 --> 01:12:24.980
These were in kind of the 10 repetition

01:12:24.980 --> 01:12:27.230
or less range, six sets.

01:12:27.230 --> 01:12:28.840
So kind of standard weight training stuff

01:12:28.840 --> 01:12:31.630
that anyone might do.

01:12:31.630 --> 01:12:35.250
But what was interesting is
that women were able to access

01:12:35.250 --> 01:12:38.070
the biggest peak in
growth hormone and IGF-1

01:12:38.070 --> 01:12:39.410
early in the exercise.

01:12:39.410 --> 01:12:40.970
So in the first 30 minutes.

01:12:40.970 --> 01:12:45.190
So what this means is even
if you just have 30 minutes,

01:12:45.190 --> 01:12:48.920
at least for women, there's
going to be a big increase

01:12:48.920 --> 01:12:51.050
in growth hormone and IGF-1
in the first 30 minutes.

01:12:51.050 --> 01:12:53.950
For men, the biggest
increase occurred later

01:12:53.950 --> 01:12:58.950
in the exercise, which was
at 60 minutes or so total.

01:12:59.570 --> 01:13:02.620
And so the sex-dependent
effects are interesting.

01:13:02.620 --> 01:13:03.510
They point to the fact

01:13:03.510 --> 01:13:05.810
that things like cortisol,
testosterone, and estrogen,

01:13:05.810 --> 01:13:07.270
which of course vary in different levels

01:13:07.270 --> 01:13:10.240
in men and women are going to impact

01:13:10.240 --> 01:13:13.570
the release of things like
IGF-1 and growth hormone.

01:13:13.570 --> 01:13:16.290
And yes, they did control
for all sorts of things

01:13:16.290 --> 01:13:18.930
like diet and they controlled for weight

01:13:18.930 --> 01:13:20.030
and prior experience.

01:13:20.030 --> 01:13:21.890
It's actually a quite nice study.

01:13:21.890 --> 01:13:25.317
If you'd like to check it
out, it's by a Pierce et al,

01:13:25.317 --> 01:13:27.940
"Growth Hormone and
Insulin Growth Factor-I

01:13:27.940 --> 01:13:29.350
Molecular Weight Isoform Response

01:13:29.350 --> 01:13:32.230
to Resistance Exercise Are Sex-Dependent"

01:13:32.230 --> 01:13:35.820
in Frontiers in Endocrinology,
fine journal in 2020.

01:13:35.820 --> 01:13:37.130
So it's quite recent.

01:13:37.130 --> 01:13:38.470
So what does this mean?

01:13:38.470 --> 01:13:41.220
This means if you're exercising

01:13:41.220 --> 01:13:43.840
and you want growth
hormone release, warm up,

01:13:43.840 --> 01:13:46.390
do the type of exercise
that we've been discussing.

01:13:47.400 --> 01:13:49.010
Women, in the first 30 minutes,

01:13:49.010 --> 01:13:50.690
is when you're going to
get the maximum benefit

01:13:50.690 --> 01:13:52.630
in terms of growth hormone and IGF-1.

01:13:52.630 --> 01:13:55.910
Men, you have to keep going
for the entire 60 minutes.

01:13:55.910 --> 01:13:58.270
So don't tap out early
if you're interested

01:13:58.270 --> 01:14:00.880
in getting the growth
hormone and IGF-1 release.

01:14:00.880 --> 01:14:02.520
And the same conditions apply

01:14:02.520 --> 01:14:04.710
about then cooling down and not making

01:14:04.710 --> 01:14:07.030
the exercise last so
long that you don't get

01:14:07.030 --> 01:14:09.840
the increase in growth
hormone the following night.

01:14:09.840 --> 01:14:13.310
My experience thus far
in doing this podcast

01:14:13.310 --> 01:14:16.160
is that people fall into
one of two categories.

01:14:16.160 --> 01:14:18.950
There are the just tell
me what to take people,

01:14:18.950 --> 01:14:22.010
the people that are really
eager to try supplements

01:14:22.010 --> 01:14:24.250
and maybe in prescription compounds.

01:14:24.250 --> 01:14:27.030
And then there are people
who are a little bit more shy

01:14:27.030 --> 01:14:28.490
about supplementation.

01:14:28.490 --> 01:14:30.080
They are more focused on what they can do

01:14:30.080 --> 01:14:32.940
with diet and behaviors
and things of that sort.

01:14:32.940 --> 01:14:34.150
I don't have a bias either way.

01:14:34.150 --> 01:14:36.580
I try and offer tools that are supported

01:14:36.580 --> 01:14:38.290
by the scientific literature.

01:14:38.290 --> 01:14:41.350
And I always point to safety margins.

01:14:41.350 --> 01:14:44.410
There are supplements that
can increase growth hormone

01:14:44.410 --> 01:14:47.330
to a considerable degree and no,

01:14:47.330 --> 01:14:49.130
these aren't growth hormone itself.

01:14:49.130 --> 01:14:51.110
Although, that of course
will increase growth hormone

01:14:51.110 --> 01:14:52.100
to a considerable degree.

01:14:52.100 --> 01:14:54.200
We will talk about
prescription drugs at the end,

01:14:54.200 --> 01:14:55.480
not just growth hormone,

01:14:55.480 --> 01:14:58.470
but some other things
that are quite prominently

01:14:58.470 --> 01:14:59.550
in use right now,

01:14:59.550 --> 01:15:03.580
in particular in the
entertainment industry.

01:15:03.580 --> 01:15:06.320
There are pretty interesting compounds.

01:15:06.320 --> 01:15:07.950
But first let's talk about supplements.

01:15:07.950 --> 01:15:10.550
So this has been known about for some time

01:15:10.550 --> 01:15:14.320
but arginine, the amino acid arginine,

01:15:14.320 --> 01:15:17.060
as well as the amino acid ornithine

01:15:17.060 --> 01:15:20.590
can increase growth hormone
levels substantially.

01:15:20.590 --> 01:15:24.660
Now, arginine has a number of effects.

01:15:24.660 --> 01:15:27.230
You can get it from food, you
can get it from supplements.

01:15:27.230 --> 01:15:30.830
Some people take it in
pill form or capsule form.

01:15:30.830 --> 01:15:34.943
Some people will actually
take it by IV, intravenously.

01:15:36.110 --> 01:15:39.650
The levels and the amounts
of arginine required

01:15:39.650 --> 01:15:42.610
to get big growth
hormone release increases

01:15:42.610 --> 01:15:43.730
is pretty substantial.

01:15:43.730 --> 01:15:46.900
So some people will take
arginine before bedtime,

01:15:46.900 --> 01:15:49.770
some people will take it before exercise.

01:15:49.770 --> 01:15:53.430
The prerequisite again
is low blood glucose.

01:15:53.430 --> 01:15:56.880
Blood glucose is high, it's
going to quash the effect.

01:15:56.880 --> 01:15:59.770
The amounts of arginine that people take

01:15:59.770 --> 01:16:04.300
are anywhere from three grams to 10 grams,

01:16:04.300 --> 01:16:05.670
or sometimes even more.

01:16:05.670 --> 01:16:09.223
Although, this is definitely
a case of more is not better.

01:16:09.223 --> 01:16:12.840
There's a threshold at
which growth hormone release

01:16:12.840 --> 01:16:14.880
is actually blunted by taking

01:16:14.880 --> 01:16:17.880
more than nine grams of arginine.

01:16:17.880 --> 01:16:20.740
Now, nine grams of arginine
orally is a lot of pills.

01:16:20.740 --> 01:16:23.070
It's at minimum nine pills.

01:16:23.070 --> 01:16:26.670
And it can cause some
GI disturbance, right?

01:16:26.670 --> 01:16:27.810
People can feel nauseous.

01:16:27.810 --> 01:16:29.110
Some people will throw it up.

01:16:29.110 --> 01:16:34.110
Some people get some constipation
or diarrhea, et cetera,

01:16:34.270 --> 01:16:35.570
or just stomachaches.

01:16:35.570 --> 01:16:38.500
I'm certainly not
suggesting people do this

01:16:38.500 --> 01:16:39.510
that they take arginine

01:16:39.510 --> 01:16:43.270
but that's the reason why most
of the studies that looked

01:16:43.270 --> 01:16:46.180
at the role of arginine
on growth hormone levels

01:16:46.180 --> 01:16:50.250
did it by IV, intravenous infusion.

01:16:50.250 --> 01:16:52.640
So what's interesting, however,

01:16:52.640 --> 01:16:57.020
is that whether or not
it's by mouth or by vein,

01:16:57.020 --> 01:17:00.230
taking arginine can dramatically increase

01:17:00.230 --> 01:17:03.390
growth hormone release and the levels

01:17:03.390 --> 01:17:07.460
or the amount of increase was anywhere

01:17:07.460 --> 01:17:12.355
from 100 on the low-end but
anywhere basically from 400

01:17:12.355 --> 01:17:14.120
to 600% above baseline.

01:17:14.120 --> 01:17:17.770
So these are huge increases
in growth hormone.

01:17:17.770 --> 01:17:19.320
Now, I've never tried arginine.

01:17:20.220 --> 01:17:22.900
Arginine is out there for a
number of different purposes.

01:17:22.900 --> 01:17:24.980
One of them is to increase growth hormone.

01:17:24.980 --> 01:17:26.970
Some of the supplements out there

01:17:26.970 --> 01:17:30.320
to increase growth hormone
include arginine and ornithine.

01:17:30.320 --> 01:17:35.240
Arginine does have the
effect of dilating arterials.

01:17:35.240 --> 01:17:38.851
And it basically increases blood supply.

01:17:38.851 --> 01:17:42.170
The arginine pathway is
involved in vasodilation.

01:17:42.170 --> 01:17:43.250
It's actually the pathway

01:17:43.250 --> 01:17:45.570
that's downstream of a lot of drugs

01:17:45.570 --> 01:17:49.090
that are used to treat things
like erectile dysfunction.

01:17:49.090 --> 01:17:51.900
And anytime people have problems

01:17:51.900 --> 01:17:55.070
with peripheral blood flow of any kind,

01:17:55.070 --> 01:18:00.070
they focus on compounds that
will either disrupt the enzymes

01:18:01.080 --> 01:18:04.020
or will adjust the levels of amino acids

01:18:04.020 --> 01:18:05.370
to get more vasodilation.

01:18:05.370 --> 01:18:07.550
So taking arginine for the purpose

01:18:07.550 --> 01:18:10.320
of increasing growth hormone
will also have the effect

01:18:10.320 --> 01:18:12.020
of dilating blood vessels

01:18:12.020 --> 01:18:13.610
and for people with blood, excuse me,

01:18:13.610 --> 01:18:17.280
with heart conditions, that
actually can be a serious issue.

01:18:17.280 --> 01:18:19.350
Now, here is something really important

01:18:19.350 --> 01:18:20.810
and interesting to note,

01:18:20.810 --> 01:18:24.930
which is that increasing arginine levels

01:18:24.930 --> 01:18:28.440
with the specific goal of
increasing growth hormone release

01:18:29.640 --> 01:18:33.460
can actually short circuit
the effects of exercise

01:18:33.460 --> 01:18:34.360
on growth hormone.

01:18:34.360 --> 01:18:35.950
Several studies that I looked at,

01:18:35.950 --> 01:18:39.800
looked at the interaction
of taking arginine

01:18:39.800 --> 01:18:43.390
and the exercise or just the arginine

01:18:43.390 --> 01:18:44.810
or just the exercise alone.

01:18:44.810 --> 01:18:47.080
And so you don't, unfortunately,

01:18:47.080 --> 01:18:48.700
if growth hormone increase is your goal,

01:18:48.700 --> 01:18:52.190
you don't unfortunately get to
increase growth hormone 800%

01:18:52.190 --> 01:18:53.880
by taking arginine and exercising.

01:18:53.880 --> 01:18:55.230
It always seems to be clamped

01:18:55.230 --> 01:18:57.630
at about 300 to 500% increases.

01:18:57.630 --> 01:18:59.220
Still large increases.

01:18:59.220 --> 01:19:00.960
So I make that point for several reasons.

01:19:00.960 --> 01:19:03.520
First of all, be aware that arginine

01:19:03.520 --> 01:19:05.640
has these other effects on vasodilation.

01:19:05.640 --> 01:19:08.230
Take those seriously if
you have a heart condition

01:19:08.230 --> 01:19:10.660
or take them seriously in any case.

01:19:10.660 --> 01:19:13.540
Second of all, you can
supplement with arginine,

01:19:13.540 --> 01:19:16.270
not exercise and get these big increases

01:19:16.270 --> 01:19:19.160
in growth hormone by
taking them before sleep.

01:19:19.160 --> 01:19:23.340
But if you're taking the
arginine before exercise,

01:19:23.340 --> 01:19:25.380
you're going to short circuit

01:19:25.380 --> 01:19:29.070
or clamp the effects of exercise
on growth hormone, okay?

01:19:29.070 --> 01:19:31.770
So it's something that one could use

01:19:31.770 --> 01:19:35.460
but it doesn't have a
synergistic effect with exercise.

01:19:35.460 --> 01:19:39.210
The two more or less cancel
each other out, not to zero,

01:19:39.210 --> 01:19:41.130
but you end up with the
same effect you would

01:19:41.130 --> 01:19:42.890
had you done one or the other.

01:19:42.890 --> 01:19:44.310
So hopefully that's clear.

01:19:44.310 --> 01:19:46.280
The other thing is if one's goal

01:19:46.280 --> 01:19:48.630
is really to increase
arginine in the blood

01:19:48.630 --> 01:19:49.510
for whatever reason,

01:19:49.510 --> 01:19:53.170
arginine may not actually
be the best way to do that.

01:19:53.170 --> 01:19:56.210
Because of the way it's
metabolized in the gut,

01:19:56.210 --> 01:19:59.430
it doesn't have access or get access

01:19:59.430 --> 01:20:01.660
to the tissues that
you're most interested in

01:20:01.660 --> 01:20:03.250
in terms of increasing growth hormone

01:20:03.250 --> 01:20:04.900
or vasodilation for that matter.

01:20:04.900 --> 01:20:06.080
And in that case,

01:20:06.080 --> 01:20:08.280
there's something else called L-citrulline

01:20:08.280 --> 01:20:11.900
which has powerful
effects on vasodilation,

01:20:11.900 --> 01:20:16.900
powerful effects potentially
on growth hormone levels

01:20:17.610 --> 01:20:19.210
via the arginine pathway.

01:20:19.210 --> 01:20:21.610
But basically L-citrulline,

01:20:21.610 --> 01:20:23.590
it acts as sort of a donor,

01:20:23.590 --> 01:20:26.560
or it's kind of a biological
prerequisite for arginine

01:20:26.560 --> 01:20:29.810
and can lead to even
bigger arginine increases

01:20:29.810 --> 01:20:32.190
than you would get if
you took arginine itself.

01:20:32.190 --> 01:20:34.700
And so L-citrulline is out there.

01:20:34.700 --> 01:20:37.030
Keep in mind that anything that dilates

01:20:37.030 --> 01:20:39.130
the blood vessels will
lower blood pressure.

01:20:39.130 --> 01:20:42.050
So L-citrulline, yes, will
lead to increase blood flow

01:20:42.050 --> 01:20:44.660
for whatever purpose
you want to use it for,

01:20:44.660 --> 01:20:47.210
whether or not that's pumps
in the gym or whatever.

01:20:48.200 --> 01:20:50.480
It also can lead to big increases

01:20:50.480 --> 01:20:52.120
in arginine and growth hormone,

01:20:52.120 --> 01:20:54.240
but it will lower blood pressure.

01:20:54.240 --> 01:20:56.180
So be aware of that.

01:20:56.180 --> 01:20:58.740
And understand that the biology
isn't so straightforward.

01:20:58.740 --> 01:21:00.430
L-citrulline may actually
be the better way

01:21:00.430 --> 01:21:03.960
to get arginine increases
than arginine itself.

01:21:03.960 --> 01:21:07.830
And ornithine can also
increase growth hormone,

01:21:07.830 --> 01:21:10.180
although that's also
through an indirect pathway.

01:21:10.180 --> 01:21:12.140
And nowadays, there isn't a lot of focus

01:21:12.140 --> 01:21:15.450
on ornithine as a way to
increase growth hormone.

01:21:15.450 --> 01:21:17.760
That was kind of all the rage in the 90s,

01:21:17.760 --> 01:21:18.760
not so much anymore.

01:21:18.760 --> 01:21:21.930
Nowadays, the people are really
in the know for this stuff

01:21:21.930 --> 01:21:23.420
tend to focus on L-citrulline.

01:21:23.420 --> 01:21:26.590
And if you're interested in
L-citrulline or arginine,

01:21:26.590 --> 01:21:30.370
I highly recommend you
go to our old friend,

01:21:30.370 --> 01:21:32.590
good friends, examine.com,

01:21:32.590 --> 01:21:35.940
because there you can
put it into their list.

01:21:35.940 --> 01:21:39.040
You can just put search
and it's totally free.

01:21:39.040 --> 01:21:41.430
And it will tell you that blood pressure

01:21:41.430 --> 01:21:42.520
will be slightly decreased.

01:21:42.520 --> 01:21:44.500
Power output in the gym will increase.

01:21:44.500 --> 01:21:46.390
There's very strong
effects on blood glucose.

01:21:46.390 --> 01:21:48.840
Fatigue is reduced notably.

01:21:48.840 --> 01:21:51.240
Big increases in nitric oxide.

01:21:51.240 --> 01:21:54.060
That's also related to the
increase in vasodilation.

01:21:54.060 --> 01:21:58.210
Plasma arginine, very high, excuse me,

01:21:58.210 --> 01:22:02.020
notable effects, very
high support for studies,

01:22:02.020 --> 01:22:04.900
which allow people more training
volume, aerobic exercise,

01:22:04.900 --> 01:22:06.450
arterial stiffness is brought down.

01:22:06.450 --> 01:22:07.920
There's a huge list of things.

01:22:07.920 --> 01:22:09.700
Increase in growth hormone.

01:22:09.700 --> 01:22:13.550
So two studies showing,
this was done double-blind.

01:22:13.550 --> 01:22:15.020
Great, you always want
to see double-blind,

01:22:15.020 --> 01:22:16.130
placebo controlled.

01:22:16.130 --> 01:22:18.990
This was only done in
males, not in females.

01:22:18.990 --> 01:22:21.800
Unfortunately, just have data from males

01:22:21.800 --> 01:22:23.800
but increases in growth hormone,

01:22:23.800 --> 01:22:27.430
it's a small, but a
real significant effect.

01:22:27.430 --> 01:22:29.330
And again, from quality studies.

01:22:29.330 --> 01:22:31.430
So there's a huge number of effects there.

01:22:32.320 --> 01:22:34.710
And some of the other kind
of more interesting ones

01:22:34.710 --> 01:22:38.620
about L-citrulline that you
might not have thought about

01:22:38.620 --> 01:22:42.000
are things like muscle oxygenation

01:22:44.140 --> 01:22:47.310
as we scroll down, decreases
in c-reactive protein.

01:22:47.310 --> 01:22:49.740
So a lot of the same things
that you might affect,

01:22:49.740 --> 01:22:52.080
expect, excuse me, from
the same sorts of compounds

01:22:52.080 --> 01:22:53.060
we saw before.

01:22:53.060 --> 01:22:56.190
The takeaway here is if you
want to increase growth hormone,

01:22:56.190 --> 01:22:57.830
think about the arginine pathway,

01:22:57.830 --> 01:23:01.110
but arginine itself might
not be the best direct route

01:23:01.110 --> 01:23:01.943
to get there.

01:23:01.943 --> 01:23:03.910
L-citrulline might be a better option.

01:23:03.910 --> 01:23:07.130
But please do consider take very seriously

01:23:07.130 --> 01:23:08.630
the effects on blood pressure.

01:23:09.520 --> 01:23:11.910
So we've been talking about big effects

01:23:11.910 --> 01:23:15.420
from supplementation or
exercise on growth hormone,

01:23:15.420 --> 01:23:17.760
this extremely powerful hormone.

01:23:17.760 --> 01:23:22.360
And one thing to note is that
the profile of growth hormone

01:23:22.360 --> 01:23:25.540
as we age, changes, I
mentioned that earlier,

01:23:25.540 --> 01:23:28.570
but it's important to
understand how it changes.

01:23:28.570 --> 01:23:30.250
One thing that's particularly
