in a couple minutes.

01:26:08.430 --> 01:26:13.140
But we have to remember how
growth hormone is released

01:26:13.140 --> 01:26:14.510
in the first place.

01:26:14.510 --> 01:26:18.040
Remember, it all starts in the
brain, in the hypothalamus.

01:26:18.040 --> 01:26:20.590
The hypothalamus is a
brain area that controls

01:26:20.590 --> 01:26:24.440
things like sexual behavior,
temperature regulation,

01:26:24.440 --> 01:26:26.840
circadian behavior, meaning
when you want to be awake

01:26:26.840 --> 01:26:30.500
and when you want to be asleep,
aggression, all of that.

01:26:30.500 --> 01:26:32.170
There are other brain areas involved too

01:26:32.170 --> 01:26:35.210
but it has a rich collection
of different neurons

01:26:35.210 --> 01:26:38.920
involved in all these
very basic functions.

01:26:38.920 --> 01:26:42.600
Now, as we talked about
the releasing hormones,

01:26:42.600 --> 01:26:44.700
the growth hormone-releasing hormone,

01:26:44.700 --> 01:26:47.330
it comes from neurons in the hypothalamus.

01:26:47.330 --> 01:26:49.750
Those then communicate with the pituitary

01:26:49.750 --> 01:26:52.980
and the pituitary releases growth hormone

01:26:52.980 --> 01:26:53.870
and then the growth hormone

01:26:53.870 --> 01:26:55.710
acts on all these
different tissues, muscle,

01:26:55.710 --> 01:26:58.433
liver, cartilage, et cetera, body fat.

01:26:59.740 --> 01:27:00.787
Makes them use energy.

01:27:00.787 --> 01:27:02.300
That's why you lose body fat

01:27:02.300 --> 01:27:03.470
when growth hormone levels are high.

01:27:03.470 --> 01:27:07.493
It makes you grow muscle,
strengthens bones, et cetera.

01:27:08.840 --> 01:27:13.690
Now, one of the things
that has a profound effect

01:27:13.690 --> 01:27:17.310
on growth hormone levels,
growth hormone release,

01:27:17.310 --> 01:27:18.810
is temperature.

01:27:18.810 --> 01:27:21.090
Now, the data on this are very strong

01:27:21.090 --> 01:27:23.280
and the data come from both animal studies

01:27:23.280 --> 01:27:25.140
and human studies.

01:27:25.140 --> 01:27:26.360
So there are a number of studies

01:27:26.360 --> 01:27:30.050
that have explored how
making animals cold or hot

01:27:30.050 --> 01:27:31.720
can increase growth hormone.

01:27:31.720 --> 01:27:35.270
And if you're guessing which
direction this is going to go,

01:27:35.270 --> 01:27:38.200
you can probably imagine
that making animals

01:27:38.200 --> 01:27:41.140
or people warmer is the way to go

01:27:41.140 --> 01:27:43.250
if you want to increase growth hormone.

01:27:43.250 --> 01:27:45.980
Now, anytime you're going
to increase temperature

01:27:45.980 --> 01:27:49.700
of yourself or anyone else
or an animal, it is risky.

01:27:49.700 --> 01:27:51.230
I want to be really clear about this.

01:27:51.230 --> 01:27:53.440
Not everyone should engage

01:27:53.440 --> 01:27:55.653
in the behaviors I'm about to describe.

01:27:57.260 --> 01:27:59.130
And I should just say
the reason it's risky

01:27:59.130 --> 01:28:01.080
is it doesn't take much
of a temperature increase

01:28:01.080 --> 01:28:03.820
in the brain to cook the
brain, to cook neurons.

01:28:03.820 --> 01:28:06.660
And after that point,
neurons can't come back.

01:28:06.660 --> 01:28:09.580
And people can die from hyperthermia.

01:28:09.580 --> 01:28:11.470
We have a much greater
range in terms of cold.

01:28:11.470 --> 01:28:13.030
You can also die of hypothermia.

01:28:13.030 --> 01:28:14.980
You can freeze to death.

01:28:14.980 --> 01:28:18.230
But you have a much greater
range of getting cold

01:28:18.230 --> 01:28:20.450
than you do warming up the brain.

01:28:20.450 --> 01:28:24.810
However, there are really
strong data pointing to the fact

01:28:24.810 --> 01:28:29.810
that sauna, AKA deliberate hyperthermia,

01:28:30.600 --> 01:28:34.060
not too high, however,
that sauna can increase

01:28:34.060 --> 01:28:37.060
the release of growth
hormone and other hormones.

01:28:37.060 --> 01:28:39.120
And what's so dramatic
about this literature

01:28:39.120 --> 01:28:42.710
is the size of the
effects that are reported.

01:28:42.710 --> 01:28:43.543
So first of all,

01:28:43.543 --> 01:28:46.400
let's talk about these
temperature increases.

01:28:46.400 --> 01:28:49.510
And yes, I will refer to
things that people can do

01:28:49.510 --> 01:28:52.370
even if you don't own a sauna

01:28:52.370 --> 01:28:54.810
because I realized not
everybody has a sauna

01:28:54.810 --> 01:28:57.060
in their backyard or
has access to a sauna.

01:28:57.060 --> 01:28:59.850
So first of all, recall our study

01:28:59.850 --> 01:29:03.610
about exercise where
warming up a few degrees

01:29:03.610 --> 01:29:08.010
before the exercise led to
bigger and quicker increases

01:29:08.010 --> 01:29:11.150
in growth hormone during
the exercise about itself.

01:29:11.150 --> 01:29:12.680
So that already point in the direction

01:29:12.680 --> 01:29:14.490
that temperature was important.

01:29:14.490 --> 01:29:17.740
Now, the degrees, no pun intended,

01:29:17.740 --> 01:29:21.680
that we're talking about
increasing body temperature

01:29:21.680 --> 01:29:25.180
is by entering saunas that are somewhere

01:29:25.180 --> 01:29:28.170
between 176 degrees Fahrenheit,

01:29:28.170 --> 01:29:30.663
so that's 80 degrees Celsius,

