Along the lines of
temperature and hormones,

01:34:29.500 --> 01:34:31.480
I just want to mention
a very recent study,

01:34:31.480 --> 01:34:32.750
it just came out.

01:34:32.750 --> 01:34:35.307
March, April, 2021,

01:34:35.307 --> 01:34:38.040
"Endocrine Effects of
Repeated Hot Thermal Stress

01:34:38.040 --> 01:34:40.520
and Cold Water Immersion
in Young Adult Men."

01:34:40.520 --> 01:34:41.530
Unfortunately, it was just in men,

01:34:41.530 --> 01:34:42.670
they didn't look at women,

01:34:42.670 --> 01:34:44.640
but nonetheless I think
the data are relevant

01:34:44.640 --> 01:34:46.640
to everybody as a general theme.

01:34:46.640 --> 01:34:48.880
This is Podstawski et al.

01:34:48.880 --> 01:34:52.520
I will put a link to
the study in the caption

01:34:52.520 --> 01:34:54.710
and they looked at testosterone,

01:34:54.710 --> 01:34:57.040
prolactin, cortisol, et cetera.

01:34:57.040 --> 01:35:00.170
And what they found was that the sauna

01:35:00.170 --> 01:35:04.190
does indeed lead to a
significant decrease in cortisol,

01:35:04.190 --> 01:35:07.080
a stress hormone, a hormone
