01:38:03.000 --> 01:38:06.120
I'd like to clarify a little
bit about what peptides are.

01:38:06.120 --> 01:38:10.860
Peptides is a really huge
category of biological compounds.

01:38:10.860 --> 01:38:13.970
Peptides are just strings
of amino acids, right?

01:38:13.970 --> 01:38:16.420
So we've talked about
L-tyrosine, arginine, ornithine.

01:38:16.420 --> 01:38:17.280
Those are amino acids.

01:38:17.280 --> 01:38:18.810
Those are individual amino acids.

01:38:18.810 --> 01:38:23.010
And those are put together
into little small peptides

01:38:23.010 --> 01:38:25.250
or they're what are called polypeptides,

01:38:25.250 --> 01:38:27.063
which are just longer peptides.

01:38:28.245 --> 01:38:31.360
It turns out that for any
substance like growth hormone

01:38:31.360 --> 01:38:32.970
or growth hormone-releasing hormone,

01:38:32.970 --> 01:38:34.560
it's made up of different amino acids

01:38:34.560 --> 01:38:35.580
in different sequences,

01:38:35.580 --> 01:38:38.710
just like your genes
are made up of As and Gs

01:38:38.710 --> 01:38:41.070
and Cs and Ts, nucleotides
in different sequences.

01:38:41.070 --> 01:38:42.323
It's like a recipe.

01:38:43.610 --> 01:38:48.130
Peptides tend to be short
sequences of amino acids

01:38:48.130 --> 01:38:51.590
that resemble a hormone enough or resemble

01:38:51.590 --> 01:38:54.300
some other peptide enough that it can lead

01:38:54.300 --> 01:38:57.140
to the similar same effects
when you inject them.

01:38:57.140 --> 01:39:01.360
So for example, we make growth
hormone-releasing hormone

01:39:01.360 --> 01:39:03.260
from our brain which
stimulates growth hormone

01:39:03.260 --> 01:39:04.093
from the pituitary.

01:39:04.093 --> 01:39:07.090
You're probably getting tired
of me saying that by now.

01:39:07.090 --> 01:39:11.660
But people now will take
things like sermorelin,

01:39:11.660 --> 01:39:16.660
S-E-R-M-O-R-E-L-I-N, sermorelin,

01:39:16.790 --> 01:39:19.570
which is not the entire peptide sequence

01:39:19.570 --> 01:39:21.510
of growth hormone-releasing hormone

01:39:21.510 --> 01:39:23.090
but it's a subset of those.

01:39:23.090 --> 01:39:24.210
And when people inject it

01:39:24.210 --> 01:39:25.520
before they go to sleep at night

01:39:25.520 --> 01:39:27.650
is typically how it's
done on an empty stomach.

01:39:27.650 --> 01:39:30.210
Then that stimulates the
release of growth hormone

01:39:30.210 --> 01:39:31.330
from the pituitary.

01:39:31.330 --> 01:39:33.560
So this is not taking growth hormone,

01:39:33.560 --> 01:39:36.060
this is taking the stimulating hormone

01:39:36.060 --> 01:39:40.210
or what's often called a
secretagogue or a mimic, all right?

01:39:40.210 --> 01:39:44.050
It causes a secretion of
the hormone that one wants.

01:39:44.050 --> 01:39:45.760
People will do this for
thyroid hormone, too.

01:39:45.760 --> 01:39:47.290
Some people are doing this

01:39:47.290 --> 01:39:49.280
by prescription with a real medical need.

01:39:49.280 --> 01:39:52.150
Other people are doing it
